      "orig": "� � One such vector space is R 2 , the set of all vectors with exactly two real number components. We depict the vector a by drawing an arrow from b the origin to the point ( a , b ) which is a units to the right of the origin and b units above it, and we call R 2 the ' x -y plane'.",
      "text": "� � One such vector space is R 2 , the set of all vectors with exactly two real number components. We depict the vector a by drawing an arrow from b the origin to the point ( a , b ) which is a units to the right of the origin and b units above it, and we call R 2 the ' x -y plane'."
    },
