      "orig": "The collection of vectors with exactly two positive real valued components is not a vector space. The sum of any two vectors in that collection is again in the collection, but multiplying any vector by, say, -5, gives a vector that's not in the collection. We say that this collection of positive vectors is closed under addition but not under multiplication.",
      "text": "The collection of vectors with exactly two positive real valued components is not a vector space. The sum of any two vectors in that collection is again in the collection, but multiplying any vector by, say, -5, gives a vector that's not in the collection. We say that this collection of positive vectors is closed under addition but not under multiplication."
